@startuml merge_conflict_to_srr_side_risk_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Merge Conflict To SRR Side Risk Signal Flow\n(merge-conflict + lamp state -> SRR side-object detection publish)

participant "Scenario/risk /\nlamp context" as SideCtx #F4F7FB
participant "SRR_FL\nside radar owner" as SRR #E8F7E8
participant "Side radar state bus" as SrrBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / lane-change users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Side-risk Inputs ==

SideCtx -> SRR : mergeConflict / riskClass\nturnLampState\npathReady
SRR -> SRR : if object input stale then\nmergeConflict = 0 / riskClass = 0
SRR -> SRR : if lamp stale then\nturnLampState = 0
SRR -> SRR : detected =\n(mergeConflict == 1 and turnLampState == 1 and riskClass >= 2) ? 1 : 0
SRR -> SRR : riskLevel = detected ? 40 + riskClass*10 : 0
SRR -> SRR : if pathReady == 0 then\nclear merge / detect / risk
note right of SRR
Representative gating inputs
- mergeConflict
- riskClass
- turnLampState
- pathReady
end note

== SRR Publish ==

SRR -> SrrBus : frmSrrFlStateMsg\nSideObjectDetected / SideRiskLevel / MergeConflict / TurnLampState
note right of SRR
Representative outputs
- SideObjectDetected
- SideRiskLevel
- MergeConflict
- TurnLampState
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

SrrBus -> Obs : side-risk readback /\nlane-change assist consumers

note over SideCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Merge conflict and lamp context reach SRR
2. SRR decides whether side-object risk is active
3. SRR publishes side detection and risk level
4. Lane-change observers consume the effective side-risk posture
end note

@enduml
